“House Of The Rising Sun” by The Animals '60s R&B style cover by Postmodern Jukebox ft. LaVance Colley.

If you’ve recently seen PMJ live on our 2025 Summer Tour, then you no doubt remember emcee LaVance Colley’s sensational performance of the traditional folk ballad, “House Of The Rising Sun” (most famously recorded by The Animals in 1964).  Here’s the official video to our classic rhythm & blues version of this timeless melody, which draws inspiration from both '60s Soul pioneers like Billy Stewart and Stax Records legends like Isaac Hayes.
